org.pojava.datetime

Class Tm

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pojava.datetime.Tm

  • public class Tm
extends Object
    This class converts a DateTime into year, month, day, hour, minute, second, millisecond, nanosecond. It is similar to the tm struct in C.
    Author:
    John Pile

      • calcTime

        public static long calcTime(int year,
            int month,
            int day,
            int hour,
            int min,
            int sec,
            int milli)
        Determine "time" in milliseconds since epoch, UTC, as of the entered local time. It is acceptable to use numbers outside of a normal range, such as a 15th month, or 64th minute.
        Parameters:
        year - calendar year
        month - calendar month
        day - calendar day
        hour - hour of day
        min - minute of hour
        sec - seconds
        milli - milliseconds
        Returns:
        time in milliseconds since epoch, UTC.
